'''Plain vanilla''' is  an [[adjective]] describing the simplest version of something, without any optional extras, basic or ordinary.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010224001515/http://www.bartleby.com/61/68/P0346850.html plain vanilla] in ''The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language: Fourth Edition. 2000.'' "Informal Lacking adornments or special features; basic or ordinary: “plain vanilla stock options; a plain vanilla wardrobe.”"</ref> In analogy with the common [[ice cream]] flavour [[vanilla]], which became widely and cheaply available with the development of artificial [[vanillin]] flavour.<ref>{{cite book |first1=Katri |last1=Hilden |first2=Tim |last2=Robinson |first4=Emma |last4=Hutchinson |last3=Currie |title=Iced: 180 Very Cool Concoctions |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=02YG2aTL89MC |accessdate=4 April 2013 |year=2006 |publisher=Murdoch Books |isbn=978-1-74045-818-4 |first3=Lee |page=15 |quote=''Vanilla has become a synonymous with 'plain'- perhaps most vanilla ice cream is flavoured with fake vanilla extract'' |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101002243/http://books.google.com/books?id=02YG2aTL89MC |archivedate=1 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>
Certain [[financial instrument]]s, such as [[put option]]s or [[call option]]s, are often described as ''plain vanilla'' options. The opposite of plain vanilla options are [[exotic option]]s.<ref>Plain vanilla on [http://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/plainvanilla.asp#axzz1bK07Gcd5 www.investopedia.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080521230407/http://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/plainvanilla.asp |date=2008-05-21 }}</ref>

==See also==
* [[Vanilla software]], is a computer software which is not customized.
* [[Vanilla sex]], sexual behavior which a culture regards as standard or conventional.

