{{multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=December 2013}} {{more citations needed|date=December 2013}} }} {{infobox person |name = Ravella Venkatrama Rao |birth_date = {{birth date|1927|1|30}} |birth_place = Gokinepally, Mudigonda, Khammamet, Hyderabad State, Andhra Pradesh |spouse = Ravella Suguna |children = Madhava Rao, Maheshwar Rao, Manohar Varma, Laxmana Varma |death_date = {{Death date and age|2013|12|10|1927|1|30}} |occupation= writer |other_names = Jayasri }} '''Ravella Venkatarama Rao''' (30 January 1927 – 10 December 2013) was a Telugu-language writer and poet. He wrote under pen-name, ''Jayasri''.<ref>[http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2013-12-11/Well-known-writer-Ravella-no-more-79121 Well-Known Writer Ravella no More - The Hans India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Life== He was born in Gokinepally village, Mudigonda, Khammamet (now Khammamm) [[Hyderabad State]]. He fought in the [[Telangana rebellion|Telangana armed struggle]] against the Nizam and feudal lords. He was jailed for four years.He is survived by wife and four sons wife name is Ravella suguna and sons
