'''Seán Ó Catháin''' ([[floruit|fl.]] 1726) was an Irish [[scribe]].
Little is known of Ó Catháin. He transcribed ''[[Trí Biorghaoithe an Bháis]]''&nbsp;– by [[Seathrún Céitinn]]&nbsp;– and ''[[Beatha Chaitríona]]'', "air forálamh an óig úasail róonoraigh fhíorchartannaidh .i. Fhroinnsais Óig a Blake mhic Tomais oíghreadh na bForbach" (for Francis Óg son of Thomas Blake of [[Furbogh|Furbogh, County Galway]]) in 1726, now BM Egerton 184. He wrote RIA 23 G 4, containing history, genealogy and poetry, sometime between 1722 and 1729. {{citation needed|date=December 2014}}
